article.headline: Boston gets 1st win vs. a Texas team since 2000
article.linkText: Celtics snap Rockets' five-game win streak
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Coach Jim O'Brien knew all about the Boston Celtics' recent struggles in Texas. "I was aware of it," O'Brien said. "When I walked in through that door into the locker room, I was thinking about it." He doesn't have to spend too much time pondering it now. Paul Pierce scored 27 points and Jiri Welsch and Walter McCarty each added 21 to help Boston beat the Houston Rockets 97-93 Sunday night, the Celtics' first win in Texas in nearly four years. Mark Blount had 10 points for the Celtics, whose last win in the state was a 104-99 victory at Dallas on Feb. 18, 2000. "It's hard to come down here and win," O'Brien said. "You're not only on the road, but you're on the road against good teams. The Rockets, Spurs and Dallas are all very strong teams and we've just been trying to get our act together. It's nice to get a win against any of these teams in Texas." Pierce said the quality of the opponents was a major reason for Boston's Texas skid. "Yes, we've just had trouble with Western Conference teams for a while," Pierce said. "When you get San Antonio, Dallas and Houston back-to-back, it's no fun either. "This was a good win for us. Our defense came up big against one of the best teams in the league." Jim Jackson had a season-high 26 points and Steve Francis 19 for Houston, which had won five straight, and six in a row over the Celtics in Houston. "They played a great game," coach Jeff Van Gundy said. "We didn't defend and our turnovers were at a high rate. We played with zero team energy." Francis had no excuses for the team's play. "First of all, we didn't come out prepared at the beginning of the game," he said. "And second of all, our shot selection was horrible, especially at crucial times. "In order to win, you've got to be able to move the ball against a good defensive-minded team like Boston and we didn't move the ball when we needed to." Cuttino Mobley had eight of his 15 points in the fourth quarter as Houston got within three points at 79-76 with 5:36 to play. But the Rockets could get no closer as the Celtics went 8-for-9 from the foul line in the closing minutes. A 10-0 run in the middle of the second quarter gave Boston a 39-26 lead with 6:06 left in the half. The Rockets went on a six-minute scoring drought, missing 11 straight shots from the field in that span. McCarty had 13 points in the second quarter and 16 at the half as Boston led 46-38. After hitting its first three 3-pointers, Houston took an early 14-7 lead. But Pierce scored 13 in the first quarter to help Boston come back to a 24-20 lead after one.

Game notes
The last time Boston won at Houston was a 108-106 victory Jan. 18, 1997. ... The Celtics tied a Rockets opponent season high with 11 3-pointers, matching Seattle's total on Nov.29 ... The 12 3-pointers were Houston's season high ... The Rockets have had a winning record in every month of this season. The last time they finished with a winning record in every month was 1993-94, when they won the NBA title.
